Company: State Department of Labor and Industries, Washington State Employees Credit Union, Court of Appeals
Description of incident: Confidential paper files from at least three tenants of the state-owned Rhodes Building were found in an unsecured recycling bin.  Some documents included names, Social Security numbers, checking account information, health information and dates of birth.  A news report claimed the documents numbered in the dozens.  Representatives for some of the organizations claimed that the files were supposed to be shredded.
